{"key":"processedPost-6406660","value":{"id":6406660,"first":6405921,"last":6406821,"when":1167370741,"utime":"12/29/06 07:39 AM","content":"Let's can the off topic preaching please.  The chemicals and salts in man made fertilizers trash the land and pollute the rivers, killing fish and rendering previously good soil barren.   There's two sides to every story, and I'm sure a forum for them too, but this isn't it.<br /><br />Sclerotia is not a waste of time at all.  I can grow half a quart of sclerotia from one quart jar of rye berries in 8 weeks.  The key is to hydrate the berries in weak coffee, and remember to add a pinch of gypsum to each jar, or use it in the soak water for the grains.<br /><br />It's easy to isolate for a good sclerotia producer on agar, and use that strain to inoculate jars for producing stones.   You can also isolate for fruiting qualities and use that strain for generating prints/fruits.<br />RR<br /><br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/06-52/737065906-Mex_a_sclerotia_a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/06-52/737065906-thumb_Mex_a_sclerotia_a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/06-52/737065901-Jalisco_fruiting.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/06-52/737065901-thumb_Jalisco_fruiting.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/06-52/737065911-jalisco.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/06-52/737065911-thumb_jalisco.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: sclerotia question - please help!!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}